  "takeaways": [
    "This artifact returns to the strict lane after separating the treatment-side TOC/ROW issue: it asks which direct-count pieces still fail to verify the non-TDC residual once the suspect treatment bundle is excluded.",
    "Read the TOC/ROW-excluded block as a diagnostic comparison, not as a replacement headline treatment.",
    "At h0, the strict missing-channel comparison starts from a much smaller residual once TOC/ROW is excluded: baseline residual \u2248 -81.18, TOC/ROW-excluded residual \u2248 -5.50.",
    "Under the TOC/ROW-excluded comparison at h0, the directly counted pieces still need to be read separately: headline direct core \u2248 -10.66, current broad loan source \u2248 5.58, private-borrower-augmented core \u2248 8.49, noncore/system diagnostic \u2248 4.32, securities \u2248 3.48, funding-adjusted net \u2248 9.90.",
    "At h0, the TOC/ROW-excluded comparison exposes a sign mismatch inside the strict lane: the residual stays negative at about -5.50, while the strict identifiable total turns positive at about 10.83.",
    "Even after excluding TOC/ROW, the direct-count verification problem remains large: strict gap share of residual \u2248 2.96, gap-after-funding share \u2248 2.84.",
    "H0 interpretation: `toc_row_exclusion_exposes_sign_mismatch_in_direct_counts`."
  ]
}
